Outside of the courthouse where the two men, Theo Martins Jackson and Willem Oosthuizen were applying for bail, after forcing Victor Rethabile Mlotshwa into a coffin and assaulting him, an unknown man was severely beaten by a mob. Apparently the beating occurred after the man threatened to stab some members of the ANC.The mob beat the man until he fell to the ground and then trampled on him and continued beating him with their fists.Afterwards they put a road signboard on him and repeatedly jumped on him while he lay on the ground.The man sustained a head injury before being rescued by the police.Willem Oosthuizen and Theo Martins Jackson have been accused of shoving Victor Rethabile Mlotshwa man into a coffin while threatening to kill him. Picture: Itumeleng EnglishSource: IOL